messages.message: @Gaurav Saini Did you get a chance to look into this? This is broken in 25.30 (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72795) as well. Could you please look as this is blocking merges and backports.
@mfichman do we need to backport this PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72768) as well
@Sayan yes, I have raised the backport PR. Waiting on CI to pass
That PR looks like its for python files, do we need something for the go files as well?
oh, nevermind not that one. This one - https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72854

I think we need both python and go changes. Yesterday I was trying to add an endpoint with only  go changes and it wasn't able to find the endpoint and that was fixed after generating the python protos.photos. I'm not 100% sure so would be good if @mfichman could weigh in

Python bindings are required if you want to use them in python services. These protos aren't used anywhere right now. Backporting that PR would break things, since it doesn't contain all the generated pbs.
And I think the python generated files were merged after the code cut, so won't need to backport the revert.
We don't _really_ need to backport it -- the Go Github action is not merge-blocking yet, and docker images are still built using Bazel instead. But it won't hurt to do it!
Link? Jenkins/Bazel CI generates the protobuf files using Bazel
Nevermind, you are right. Its a different issue with CI :man-facepalming:
The CI failures would most likely be unrelated. For the backport PR the go tests passed but CI is failing on different tests in each run - https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72854.
Finally CI passed, backport is merged.
